<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure the availability of port reception facilities adequate to meet the needs of the ships normally using the port without causing undue delay to ships. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et sadamates on olemas vastuv&otilde;tuseadmed, mis on piisavad selleks, et t&auml;ita tavaliselt sadamat k&uuml;lastavate laevade vajadused neile asjatuid viivitusi p&otilde;hjustamata. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> To achieve adequacy, the reception facilities shall be capable of receiving the types and quantities of ship-generated waste and cargo residues from ships normally using that port, taking into account the operational needs of the users of the port, the size and the geographical location of the port, the type of ships calling at that port and the exemptions provided for under Article 9. </inglise>
