<inglise> Member States may decide that the information will be notified to the operator of the port reception facility, who will forward it to the relevant authority. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad otsustada, et teavitatakse sadama vastuv&otilde;tuseadmete k&auml;itajat, kes edastab teabe asjaomasele asutusele. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The information referred to in paragraph 1 shall be kept on board at least until the next port of call and shall upon request be made available to the Member States' authorities. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud teavet s&auml;ilitatakse pardal v&auml;hemalt kuni j&auml;rgmise k&uuml;lastatava sadamani ning vastava taotluse peale antakse see liikmesriikide asutuste kasutusse. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Delivery of ship-generated waste </inglise>
<eesti> Laevaheitmete &uuml;leandmine </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The master of a ship calling at a Community port shall, before leaving the port, deliver all ship-generated waste to a port reception facility. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;henduse sadamat k&uuml;lastava laeva kapten annab enne sadamast lahkumist k&otilde;ik laevaheitmed &uuml;le sadama vastuv&otilde;tuseadmetesse. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding paragraph 1, a ship may proceed to the next port of call without delivering the ship-generated waste, if it follows from the information given in accordance with Article 6 and Annex II, that there is sufficient dedicated storage capacity for all ship-generated waste that has been accumulated and will be accumulated during the intended voyage of the ship until the port of delivery. </inglise>
<eesti> Olenemata l&otilde;ike 1 s&auml;tetest v&otilde;ib laev s&otilde;ita edasi j&auml;rgmisse sadamasse laevaheitmeid &uuml;le andmata, kui artikli 6 ja II lisa kohaselt esitatud informatsioonist ilmneb, et olemasolevad eriladustamisruumid on piisavad juba kogunenud ja kavandatava reisi ajal kogunevate laevaheitmete ladustamiseks kuni &uuml;leandmissadamasse j&otilde;udmiseni. </eesti>
<inglise> If there are good reasons to believe that adequate facilities are not available at the intended port of delivery, or if this port is unknown, and that there is therefore a risk that the waste will be discharged at sea, the Member State shall take all necessary measures to prevent marine pollution, if necessary by requiring the ship to deliver its waste before departure from the port. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui on alust arvata, et kavandatavas &uuml;leandmissadamas ei ole piisavaid seadmeid v&otilde;i kui &uuml;leandmissadam ei ole teada ja seega on oht, et j&auml;&auml;tmed juhitakse merre, v&otilde;tab liikmesriik k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed meresaaste v&auml;ltimiseks, n&otilde;udes vajaduse korral, et laev annaks j&auml;&auml;tmed &uuml;le enne sadamast lahkumist. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Paragraph 2 shall apply without prejudice to more stringent delivery requirements for ships adopted in accordance with international law. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;iget 2 kohaldatakse ilma, et see piiraks rahvusvahelise &otilde;iguse kohaselt vastu v&otilde;etud rangemaid n&otilde;udeid laevaheitmete &uuml;leandmise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> Fees for ship-generated waste </inglise>
<eesti> Laevaheitmete eest v&otilde;etavad tasud </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that the costs of port reception facilities for ship-generated waste, including the treatment and disposal of the waste, shall be covered through the collection of a fee from ships. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et laevaheitmete vastuv&otilde;tuseadmetega sadamates, sealhulgas laevaheitmete k&auml;itlemise ja k&otilde;rvaldamisega seotud kulud kaetakse laevadelt sissen&otilde;utavate tasudega. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The cost recovery systems for using port reception facilities shall provide no incentive for ships to discharge their waste into the sea. </inglise>
<eesti> Sadama vastuv&otilde;tuseadmete kasutuskulude eest tasumise s&uuml;steem ei motiveeri laevaheitmete juhtimist merre. </eesti>
<inglise> To this end the following principles shall apply to ships other than fishing vessels and recreational craft authorised to carry no more than 12 passengers: </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks kohaldatakse laevade suhtes, mis ei ole kalalaevad ega kuni 12 reisija l&otilde;bus&otilde;idulaevad, j&auml;rgmisi p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) all ships calling at a port of a Member State shall contribute significantly to the costs referred to in paragraph 1, irrespective of actual use of the facilities. </inglise>
<eesti> a) k&otilde;ik liikmesriigi sadamaid k&uuml;lastavad laevad annavad m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rse panuse l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud kulude kandmisse olenemata sellest, kas nad tegelikult seadmeid kasutavad. </eesti>
<inglise> Arrangements to this effect may include incorporation of the fee in the port dues or a separate standard waste fee. </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks v&otilde;etavate meetmete raames v&otilde;ib tasud arvata sadamamaksude hulka v&otilde;i kehtestada eraldi kindlasummalise j&auml;&auml;tmetasu. </eesti>
<inglise> The fees may be differentiated with respect to, inter alia, the category, type and size of the ship; </inglise>
<eesti> Tasud v&otilde;ib diferentseerida ka olenevalt laeva kategooriast, liigist ja suurusest; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the part of the costs which is not covered by the fee referred to in subparagraph (a), if any, shall be covered on the basis of the types and quantities of ship-generated waste actually delivered by the ship; </inglise>
<eesti> b) kui punktis a osutatud tasu ei kata k&otilde;iki kulusid, kaetakse kulude katmata osa laeva poolt tegelikult &uuml;le antud laevaheitmete liigi ja koguste p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) fees may be reduced if the ship's environmental management, design, equipment and operation are such that the master of the ship can demonstrate that it produces reduced quantities of ship-generated waste. </inglise>
<eesti> c) tasusid v&otilde;ib v&auml;hendada, kui laeva haldamine, ehitus, seadmed ja k&auml;itus on keskkonna suhtes sellised, et laeva kapten saab t&otilde;endada, et laevas tekitatud laevaheitmete kogused on tavalisest v&auml;iksemad. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to ensure that the fees are fair, transparent, non-discriminatory and reflect the costs of the facilities and services made available and, where appropriate, used, the amount of the fees and the basis on which they have been calculated should be made clear for the port users. </inglise>
<eesti> Tagamaks, et tasud on &otilde;iglased, mittediskrimineerivad ja l&auml;bipaistvad ning kajastavad olemasolevate ja vajaduse korral ka kasutatavate seadmete ja teenuste kulusid, peavad tasude summad ja nende arvutamise alused olema sadama kasutajate jaoks selged. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall, within three years of the date referred to in Article 16(1), submit a report to the European Parliament and to the Council, evaluating the impact of the variety of cost recovery systems adopted in accordance with paragraph 2 on the marine environment and waste flow patterns. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon esitab Euroopa Parlamendile ja n&otilde;ukogule kolme aasta jooksul p&auml;rast artikli 16 l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud kuup&auml;eva aruande, milles hindab erinevate l&otilde;ike 2 kohaselt kehtestatud kulude eest tasumise s&uuml;steemide m&otilde;ju merekeskkonnale ja j&auml;&auml;tmete liikumisele. </eesti>
<inglise> This report shall be drawn up in liaison with the competent authorities of the Member States and representatives of ports. </inglise>
